{{SupportPage|vendor=Linksys|model=WRT55AG}} WRT55AG v2 serial numbers appear to start with '''MDJ1'''. "WRTA-119AG_V01", "109-102-4500", and a date code of '''0449''' is silkscreened on one particular WRT55AGv2's board. {{WiFiCert|W002867|10/15/2004}} This device may use U-NII-2 channels but does not implement DFS since it predates the FCC requirements. ==Additional external links== *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/wiki/index.php/Supported_Devices On the '''DD-WRT''' Wiki's Supported Devices Table] (though, it's unsupported) ==Probable used PSU(s)== The power supply included with the device is a ('''Linksys''' branded, model AD 5/2.5C) '''Leader Electronics''' MT15-5050250-A1. {{hasPowerSupply |brand=Leader Electronics |model=MT15-5050250-A1 |revision=(Linksys AD 5/2.5C) |input_v=100-120 |input_a=0.5 |input_c=AC |input_hz=50/60 |input_conn=NEMA 1-15P |output_v=5 |output_a=2.5 |output_c=DC |output_conn=barrel |style=large, vertical |manuf_country=China }}
